article.description: Amber Jacobs scored a season-high 28 points as Boston College (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) beat Miami 84-77 on Saturday.
article.headline: Jacobs, Gottstein too much for Hurricanes
article.linkText: Late 13-0 run fuels BC's win over Miami
article.story:
BOSTON (AP) -- Amber Jacobs scored a season-high 28 points as Boston College (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) beat Miami 84-77 on Saturday.

	   Becky Gottstein added 24 points and nine rebounds. Brianne
Stepherson had career-high 13 assists and six points for the Eagles
(19-7, 11-4 Big East).

	   Meghan Saake paced Miami (15-11, 7-8) with 24 points, and Tamara
James added 23.

	   The Eagles led for the majority of the game and held a 39-33
halftime edge.

	   The Hurricanes pulled ahead 77-71 with three minutes left before
the Eagles retook the lead with a 13-0 run.

	   Gottstein hit a three-point play to give the Eagles a 78-77 lead
with 1:28 remaining. Jacobs followed with a 3-pointer with 31
seconds left to help seal it.
